History and Trivia:

-------------------


The TI99/2 BASIC Computer was an attempt at producing a cheap ($100) computer. TI started 
designing it in the summer of 1982, it was first introduced in January 1983, and it was 
abandoned, before entering production, by April 1983.


It featured a TMS9995 microprocessor (with on-line timer and 256-byte RAM), 4kb of RAM, 24kb 
